<p>
	
	Well, we get a line.<br/><br/>
	
	Now, let's consider another equation \(y = 1-2x+x^2\)  <br/><br/>
	
	In math, it's a common practice to use terms like x, y or z. Because, imagine writing elaborate names in the paper, it's tiring and takes a lot of space.<br/><br/>
	
	I would leave what that equation calculates to your imaginations. It could be the days taken by George to win the war, or it could be the velocity of a ball at a given time.<br/><br/>
	
	Now, when we input the values of x, we see a graph that's a bit more complicated. Why's that so? In the next graph, try adding x terms with power.<br/><br/>
